# Smokebook template — mandatory shape

Every **smokebook** or **smoke-runbook** produced in this repo (typically under `docs/handoff/`, or feature-scoped `docs/*SMOKE*.md`) **MUST** follow [`docs/handoff/SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/handoff/SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md).

**When Andrew runs it:** only when the feature is **DONE** ([`smoke-when-done.mdc`](smoke-when-done.mdc)). Agents complete Playwright coverage + automated gates first. Smokebooks target **new UX + hardware/human judgment** — not regression re-proof.

## Required structure

1. **Header block** — feature name; `Branch:`; `Tip commit:` (linked); `Preview:` (markdown link to real Vercel alias). No overall verdict in the header.
2. **Per test item** (in order) — `### N. <title>` → `**Action:**` (detailed steps) → `**Expect:**` → `**Ignore this run:**` (always present; `Nothing.` if none) → separate `- [ ] PASS`, `- [ ] FAIL`, `- [ ] PARTIAL`, `- [ ] N/A with notes`, and `- [ ] SKIP` → `**Notes:**`. Checkboxes MUST each be on their own line with a blank line before the list and after it, or they won't render. Per-item state is PASS / FAIL / PARTIAL / N/A with notes / SKIP; none checked = not-yet-run/missed (distinct from SKIP and N/A with notes). **PARTIAL** = partially working — some sub-checks pass and others fail; **Notes must spell out exactly what worked vs what didn't** (distinct from FAIL = wholly broken / primary expectation not met). **N/A with notes** = item does not apply as written for this run/configuration (feature absent or setup cannot exercise it); **Note explaining why is required** (distinct from SKIP = valid test deliberately not run). SKIP requires a reason in Notes.

   ```markdown
   **Action:** ...
   **Expect:** ...
   **Ignore this run:** ...

   - [ ] PASS
   - [ ] FAIL
   - [ ] PARTIAL
   - [ ] N/A with notes
   - [ ] SKIP

   **Notes:**
   ```

3. **Cross-branch / post-merge** section stub when the smoke spans merges.

4. **`## Overall result`** — final section at the **bottom** of the smokebook (after feature items and any cross-branch block), with **both** `- [ ] PASS` and `- [ ] FAIL` on separate lines (blank line before/after the list). Andrew fills this last after working top-to-bottom through all items.

5. **Comprehensive pre-master smoke — both themes (F5b, Andrew 2026-06-12).** The **pre-master comprehensive smoke** (full-site / MASTER-CUT style run before merge to `master`) MUST exercise **every in-scope item in both light and dark** color schemes — Andrew wants to have seen every surface in both themes before a master cut. Per-branch feature smokebooks are **not** required to duplicate all items in both themes unless that branch explicitly scopes theme work. Record as paired sub-items or a single item whose **Action** says *"Repeat in light, then dark"*; PASS only if both themes pass. See [`docs/handoff/SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md`](../../docs/handoff/SMOKEBOOK-TEMPLATE.md) § Comprehensive pre-master smoke.

Do not ship one-line actions, combined pass/fail lines, or items missing **Ignore this run**.

## HARD RULE — preview URLs are fetched, never guessed

Per-branch Vercel preview aliases include an **unpredictable truncated hash** for long branch names (e.g. `tutoring-notes-git-feat-wb-repla-e77c07-...`). The hash **cannot** be reconstructed from the branch name.

**Agents MUST obtain the URL from the Vercel MCP** (read-only — no greenlight required):

1. Call `list_deployments` for project `tutoring-notes` (use the configured team id).
2. Find the deployment whose `meta.githubCommitRef` matches the branch under test.
3. Set the preview URL to `https://<meta.branchAlias>` in the smokebook header.

Only if the MCP is unavailable: placeholder `Preview: <unverified — confirm in Vercel dashboard>` and tell Andrew to fix before smoke.

**Never** invent or pattern-match a `tutoring-notes-git-*` URL from the branch slug.

## Orchestrator obligation

Any dispatch prompt that asks a subagent to **produce a smokebook** MUST:

- Reference this template, [`smoke-when-done.mdc`](smoke-when-done.mdc) (Andrew smokes **once** when DONE), and the fetch-don't-guess preview rule.
- Include the **verified** `branchAlias` URL when the orchestrator already fetched it (or dispatch a read-only MCP lookup first).
- Scope items to **human judgment / hardware** — cite `[automated: <file> › <test>]` in Notes for anything Playwright already covers.

See also [`.cursor/rules/orchestrator-discipline.mdc`](orchestrator-discipline.mdc) and [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) § Merging convention.
